
An utility written using clojure and babashka to rename pdf files and create the corresponding .md files based on doi
To be run under linux 
Written to replace a number of bash scripts and learn clojure and babashka.


Commands:
Usage: bbnote <command> <options>
------------------------------------------------------------------
examples:
run1             -p dirname      -f filename.pdf                 rename one pdf  and make md file
runall           -p dirname                                      rename all pdfs in the directory and make md files
run1doi          -p dirname      -f filename.pdf         -d doi  rename one pdf based on provided doi and make md file
rename&          -p dirname                                      rename all pdfs with & in the name in the directory and the corresponding md files
removesp         -p dirname                                      rename all pdfs in the directory replacing spaces with underscores
------------------------------------------------------------------
Options:
------------------------------------------------------------------
  -p, --path       path to directory with pdf files
  -f, --pdf        pdf file name
  -d, --doi        doi of the paper
  -h, --help false print help
